title: Demotech Participates in NRRA National Conference 2015
text:
Demotech, Inc.
COLUMBUS, Ohio , Oct. 7, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Demotech, Inc., a Gold sponsor and longtime supporter of the National Risk Retention Association (NRRA), recently participated in a panel discussing "Strategies for Capital in a Difficult Market." The panel was moderated by John Prescott , Co-managing partner, Johnson Lambert LLP.
According to Joe Petrelli , President and co-founder, Demotech, Inc., capital for start-ups, including risk retention groups, is readily available for prospective entrants that have a strong business plan and an experienced management team.
About Demotech, Inc.
Demotech, Inc. is a financial analysis firm located in Columbus , Ohio. Since 1985, Demotech, Inc. has been serving the insurance industry by providing actuarial consulting as well as accurate and proven Financial Stability Ratings Â® (FSRs) for Property & Casualty insurance companies and Title underwriters. FSRs are a leading indicator of the financial stability of an insurer. The rating process provides an objective baseline as well as insight as to the financial stability of an insurer. Demotech levels the playing field by offering FSRs to insurers of all sizes. Visit www.demotech.com for more information.
About the National Risk Retention Association
The NRRA is a nonprofit 5019(c)6 trade association dedicated to protecting the rights of owner insureds and representing the risk retention group and purchasing group industry.
